# [GREEN](../wg/green.html)

## Summary

The GREEN working group met at IETF 126 to discuss the progress of its core deliverables and several related proposals. The chairs (Rob Wilton and Diego Lopez) provided a status update, noting steady progress on the adopted drafts since IETF 125. The session covered updates on working group documents including terminology, use cases, framework, and the base device YANG model. Additionally, the group discussed a potential controller-level YANG model, several new API and utilization proposals (PETRA, ISAC), cryptographic data provenance, PIM eco-mode extensions, recent Hackathon results, and IPFIX-based energy export mechanisms.

