### Terminology for Energy Efficiency Network Management
* **Presenter:** Chin
* **Slides:** [Terminology for Energy Efficiency  Network Management](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-green-terminology-for-energy-efficiency-network-management-00)
* **Draft:** `draft-ietf-green-terminology` (v02)
* **Key Updates:**
  * Aligned terminology with the framework and YANG modules.
  * Incorporated *nameplate power* (from RFC 7310) and *power factor* (defined as a percentage between 0 and 1, defaulting to 1 for DC sources).
  * Refined the definition of *Energy Management System* (EMS) by removing the carbon reporting node as it sits outside the WG charter.
* **Discussion:** The authors will migrate the individual repository to the working group repository with the chairs' assistance. The draft will continue to progress in parallel with the other core deliverables.

